6 : ABSTRACT
This major project presents RetailERP, a web-based enterprise solution developed to digitize and unify core retail operations in a single platform. The objective of the work is to replace fragmented and manual workflows with a secure, reliable, and role-driven system that can handle day-to-day business transactions with auditability.

I designed and implemented the solution using ASP.NET Core 8, C#, SQL Server, and Entity Framework Core. The platform includes authentication and authorization, master data management, stock transaction ledger, POS billing, multi-mode payment handling, return and refund workflows, loyalty and coupon logic, purchase flow, dashboard insights, and audit trail support. The system also includes production-oriented capabilities like structured logging, health and readiness endpoints, operational runbook guidance, and deployment support.

Testing was performed through a hybrid strategy. I used automated test suites for service logic, integration behavior, security regression, and reliability checks, and I complemented this with structured manual testing for operational workflows and user experience. This approach improved confidence in critical areas such as billing correctness, stock consistency, role boundaries, and deployment stability.

The project demonstrates practical viability as a strong retail ERP foundation. It is not only a feature implementation project, but also a real engineering exercise involving planning, development, testing, deployment troubleshooting, and operational hardening.


